Forgive me, but I feel I'm not expressing myself clearly.

The following facts are assumed:

Rocks attack vessels approaching the island.
Birds will cause superficial injury to individuals on or approaching the Island.
Individuals die or go missing on the island.
There is some sort of entity on the island.


Given these facts, a lost, confused seaman, likely suffering from hunger, thirst and sleep deprivation, has come to the conclusion that the birds are there explicitly to protect humans.

Given the same facts, I, as a reader, do not infer the same thing. My reading of this SCP gives me a different impression of it's purpose than the impressions of characters in it. Although this, in and of itself, is not necessarily a bad thing, for me it doesn't work in this instance.







